larius, a native of Arpinum, of obscure family, first distinguished himself by his valour at the siege of Numantia (B.c. 134). He gained his first office—that of tribune—in Rc. 119. Others followed, though slowly, and in B.c. 109 he went to Africa as legate of Metellus in the Jugurthine War. Consul two years later, he was elevated to the supreme command, and brought the conflict to a close in Rc. 106 by the capture of the Numidian monarch.
